# -- Graph Publishing / Sveltia CMS (F27) ---------------------------------------
# Model a website directly in the graph — pages as connected nodes — and publish
# a static, graph-powered site. Competes with markdown docs tools (Docusaurus/
# MkDocs/GitBook) but powered by the triple framework and offline for authoring.
# Graph-first: graph is source of truth -> export markdown+frontmatter to content/
# in THIS repo -> Sveltia CMS (external, un-forked) edits -> a /docs route group in
# the main app renders the pages (prerendered via adapter-static) -> Cloudflare
# Pages. Hosting: served alongside the app at Reckons.AI/docs now; a docs.reckons.ai
# subdomain can point at the same /docs build later. See plan "Sveltia CMS Publishing".

kb:graph-publishing rdf:type ktype:Feature ;
               rdfs:label   "Graph Publishing (Sveltia CMS)" ;
               kpred:has-status   "planned" ;
               kpred:feature-id   "F27" ;
               kpred:description  "Publish WebPage graph nodes as a static, graph-powered docs site served at Reckons.AI/docs (self-contained, in the main app — not a separate repo). Graph-first: nodes export to content/<section>/<slug>.md (frontmatter + body) plus graph.json; Sveltia CMS (external bundle, un-forked) edits the files; a prerendered /docs route group renders them via mdsvex; Cloudflare Pages deploys. Hybrid body: excerpt in graph, long-form markdown in Git. Offline-capable authoring and .zip export. Future: docs.reckons.ai subdomain over the same build." ;
               kpred:has-phase    kb:gp-phase-1 ;
               kpred:has-phase    kb:gp-phase-2 ;
               kpred:has-phase    kb:gp-phase-3 ;
               kpred:has-phase    kb:gp-phase-4 ;
               kpred:depends-on   kb:knowledge-graph ;
               kpred:depends-on   kb:repo-ingest ;
               kpred:hosting      "Served at Reckons.AI/docs (route group in the main app, prerendered via adapter-static). Future: docs.reckons.ai subdomain over the same /docs build." ;
               kpred:principle    "Graph/TTL + Reckoning is the PRIMARY authoring surface. AI-generated page content is directly editable in the graph; content/*.md is a generated, trailing by-product. Sveltia editing is a secondary convenience (round-trips back into the graph)." ;
               kpred:principle    "A markdown alignment check keeps content/*.md honest against the graph: CI regenerates markdown from the WebPage nodes and flags any committed .md that drifts (edited outside the graph, or graph changed without re-publish) — mirroring the Reckons.AI Graph Alignment Check." ;
               kpred:supports     "Embeddable images (Sveltia media_folder) and the rest of Sveltia's CMS widgets remain available for hand-editing." ;
               kpred:credits      "Sveltia CMS — github.com/sveltia/sveltia-cms (MIT). Used as an external dependency; consider sponsoring." .

kb:webpage-entity rdf:type   ktype:Feature ;
               rdfs:label   "WebPage Entity" ;
               kpred:has-status   "functional" ;
               kpred:feature-id   "F27.0" ;
               kpred:description  "Dedicated ktype:WebPage entity type with page: metadata (slug, section, template, status, nav, excerpt, body). Reuses nav:order for position, skos:broader for the site tree, nav:next/prev for sequence, skos:related for cross-links. src/lib/rdf/page.ts builds an ordered SitePage[]." ;
               kpred:part-of      kb:graph-publishing .

kb:gp-phase-1  rdf:type      ktype:Phase ;
               rdfs:label    "Phase 1 — WebPage model (offline, graph-only)" ;
               kpred:has-status   "functional" ;
               kpred:description  "ktype:WebPage type + page: predicates; entity-types registration; isMetaPredicate hides page:* from graph edges; page.ts model. Node-panel authoring affordance pending." ;
               kpred:part-of      kb:graph-publishing .

kb:gp-phase-2  rdf:type      ktype:Phase ;
               rdfs:label    "Phase 2 — Static export + in-app /docs route" ;
               kpred:has-status   "scaffolded" ;
               kpred:description  "src/lib/publish/site-export.ts serializes pages to markdown/frontmatter + graph.json; offline .zip export via fflate. A /docs route group in the main app renders content/*.md via mdsvex, prerendered under adapter-static (hybrid SPA + prerendered /docs). No separate theme repo." ;
               kpred:part-of      kb:graph-publishing ;
               kpred:depends-on   kb:gp-phase-1 .

kb:gp-phase-3  rdf:type      ktype:Phase ;
               rdfs:label    "Phase 3 — GitHub publish + Sveltia /admin" ;
               kpred:has-status   "scaffolded" ;
               kpred:description  "Sveltia /admin now shipped in the app (static/admin/index.html + config.yml, external CDN bundle) and served at Reckons.AI/admin; a starter content/docs/welcome.md seeds the collection. publishSiteToGitHub PUTs content/ to this repo (reuses parseRepoUrl + githubToken). Remaining: deploy sveltia-cms-auth (GitHub OAuth), markdown->graph round-trip import, and the markdown alignment check (CI regenerates content/*.md from the graph and flags drift)." ;
               kpred:part-of      kb:graph-publishing ;
               kpred:has-setup    kb:sveltia-cms-setup ;
               kpred:depends-on   kb:gp-phase-2 .

kb:gp-phase-4  rdf:type      ktype:Phase ;
               rdfs:label    "Phase 4 — Graph-powered site features" ;
               kpred:has-status   "planned" ;
               kpred:description  "Interactive graph view on the published site (from graph.json), search, related pages, prev/next — the differentiation vs plain markdown docs tools." ;
               kpred:part-of      kb:graph-publishing ;
               kpred:depends-on   kb:gp-phase-3 .

kb:gp-authoring rdf:type     ktype:Concept ;
               rdfs:label    "Docs authoring surface" ;
               kpred:part-of      kb:graph-publishing ;
               kpred:description  "Website/docs settings live on the Graph page (the manage/switch surface). Reckoning (Situation-Target-Proposal) is a first-class way to draft/edit page content; AI-generated content is directly editable in the graph before it becomes a page." ;
               kpred:has-status   "planned" .

kb:sveltia-cms-setup rdf:type ktype:Concept ;
               rdfs:label    "Sveltia CMS — Setup (GitHub OAuth)" ;
               kpred:part-of      kb:graph-publishing ;
               kpred:description  "Wire the /admin content manager. The CMS entry (static/admin/index.html) + config (static/admin/config.yml) ship in the app and are served at Reckons.AI/admin. GitHub login uses sveltia-cms-auth, a small Cloudflare Worker." ;
               kpred:setup-step   "1. Deploy sveltia-cms-auth: github.com/sveltia/sveltia-cms-auth (Cloudflare Worker reckons-sveltia-cms-auth, mapped to admin.reckons.ai). DONE." ;
               kpred:setup-step   "2. Create a GitHub OAuth App: Settings > Developer settings > OAuth Apps. Homepage https://reckons.ai; Authorization callback URL https://admin.reckons.ai/callback. MANUAL — a human must do this in the GitHub UI." ;
               kpred:setup-step   "3. Set the worker's GITHUB_CLIENT_ID / GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET vars (and ALLOWED_DOMAINS=reckons.ai) to the OAuth App credentials. TOOLED — paste the OAuth App's Client ID/Secret into SVELTIA_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID / SVELTIA_GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET / SVELTIA_ALLOWED_DOMAINS in .env (see .env.example), then run scripts/sveltia-auth-secrets.sh, which pushes them to the worker via `wrangler secret put`." ;
               kpred:setup-step   "4. backend.base_url in static/admin/config.yml points at https://admin.reckons.ai. DONE." ;
               kpred:setup-step   "5. Visit https://reckons.ai/admin/ and Login with GitHub" ;
               kpred:alt          "Local editing without the worker: npx @sveltia/cms-proxy-server, then enable local_backend: true in config.yml" ;
               kpred:note         "/admin is a standalone static page, so the app's strict CSP does not apply; Sveltia reaches api.github.com and the worker directly." ;
               kpred:note         "Readiness audit (2026-07-01): curl -sI https://admin.reckons.ai/auth, /callback, and / all return a bare Cloudflare 404 (server: cloudflare, cf-ray present, no worker-specific body) — the hostname resolves through Cloudflare but no request is reaching the sveltia-cms-auth Worker logic yet. Re-check the Worker Route/binding for admin.reckons.ai once step 2/3 credentials are set, since a correctly routed worker should redirect GET /auth to GitHub even before secrets exist." ;
               kpred:note         "static/admin/index.html now loads a version-pinned Sveltia bundle (@sveltia/cms@0.169.1) instead of an unpinned \"latest\" CDN URL, so upgrades are deliberate. static/media/ (config.yml media_folder) was missing and has been created with a .gitkeep." .

